          "id": "2.2",
          "title": "Boolean Expressions",
          "unit": 2,
          "source": "Unit2_Detailed_Tutorials.md",
          "body": "### What You Are Learning\n\nYou are learning how to create expressions that evaluate to `true` or `false`.\n\n### Relational Operators\n\n```java\n<    less than\n<=   less than or equal to\n>    greater than\n>=   greater than or equal to\n==   equal to\n!=   not equal to\n```\n\n### Worked Example\n\n```java\nint score = 85;\nboolean passing = score >= 70;\n```\n\n`passing` is `true`.\n\n### Range Checks\n\nIncorrect Java:\n\n```java\n0 <= score <= 100\n```\n\nCorrect:\n\n```java\nscore >= 0 && score <= 100\n```\n\n### Boundary Values\n\nFor:\n\n```java\nscore >= 70\n```\n\nTest:\n\n```text\n69 -> false\n70 -> true\n71 -> true\n```\n\n### Practice\n\nWrite Boolean expressions for:\n\n1. `age` is at least 13.\n2. `n` is even.\n3. `score` is outside 0 through 100.\n4. `word` is not equal to `\"quit\"`.\n\nAnswers:\n\n```java\nage >= 13\nn % 2 == 0\nscore < 0 || score > 100\n!word.equals(\"quit\")\n```"
