          "id": "2.5",
          "title": "Compound Boolean Expressions",
          "unit": 2,
          "source": "Unit2_Detailed_Tutorials.md",
          "body": "### What You Are Learning\n\nYou are learning to combine Boolean expressions.\n\n### Operators\n\n```java\n&&   and\n||   or\n!    not\n```\n\n### Truth Rules\n\n`a && b` is true only when both are true.\n\n`a || b` is true when at least one is true.\n\n`!a` flips true to false and false to true.\n\n### Short-Circuit Evaluation\n\nJava may skip the right side.\n\nFor `&&`:\n\n```java\nx != 0 && 10 / x > 2\n```\n\nIf `x != 0` is false, Java does not evaluate `10 / x`.\n\nFor `||`:\n\n```java\nscore == 100 || bonus / attempts > 2\n```\n\nIf `score == 100` is true, Java skips the right side.\n\n### Common Mistake\n\nIncorrect:\n\n```java\nif (x == 1 || 2 || 3)\n```\n\nCorrect:\n\n```java\nif (x == 1 || x == 2 || x == 3)\n```\n\n### Practice\n\nPredict:\n\n```java\nint x = 0;\nboolean ok = x != 0 && 12 / x > 3;\n```\n\nAnswer: `false`, no run-time error because of short-circuiting."
