          "title": "while Loops",
          "unit": 2,
          "source": "Unit2_Detailed_Tutorials.md",
          "body": "### What You Are Learning\n\nYou are learning condition-controlled repetition.\n\n### Pattern\n\n```java\ninitialization;\nwhile (condition)\n{\n    body;\n    update;\n}\n```\n\n### Worked Example\n\n```java\nint k = 1;\nwhile (k <= 5)\n{\n    System.out.print(k + \" \");\n    k++;\n}\n```\n\nOutput:\n\n```text\n1 2 3 4 5\n```\n\n### Trace Table\n\n```text\nk before condition | condition | print | k after update\n1                  | true      | 1     | 2\n2                  | true      | 2     | 3\n3                  | true      | 3     | 4\n4                  | true      | 4     | 5\n5                  | true      | 5     | 6\n6                  | false     | stop  |\n```\n\n### Infinite Loop\n\n```java\nint k = 1;\nwhile (k <= 5)\n{\n    System.out.println(k);\n}\n```\n\n`k` never changes.\n\n### Practice\n\nWrite a while loop that prints powers of 2 less than 100:\n\n```text\n1 2 4 8 16 32 64\n```\n\nPossible answer:\n\n```java\nint n = 1;\nwhile (n < 100)\n{\n    System.out.print(n + \" \");\n    n *= 2;\n}\n```"
