          "source": "Unit2_Detailed_Tutorials.md",
          "body": "### What You Are Learning\n\nYou are learning count-controlled repetition.\n\n### Pattern\n\n```java\nfor (initialization; condition; update)\n{\n    body;\n}\n```\n\n### Worked Example\n\n```java\nfor (int i = 0; i < 4; i++)\n{\n    System.out.print(i);\n}\n```\n\nOutput:\n\n```text\n0123\n```\n\n### Counting Iterations\n\nLoop:\n\n```java\nfor (int i = 10; i > 1; i -= 3)\n```\n\nValues:\n\n```text\n10, 7, 4\n```\n\nThree iterations.\n\n### Common Off-by-One Patterns\n\nPrint 1 through 10:\n\n```java\nfor (int i = 1; i <= 10; i++)\n```\n\nPrint indexes of an array:\n\n```java\nfor (int i = 0; i < arr.length; i++)\n```\n\n### Practice\n\nWrite loops for:\n\n1. 0 through 9.\n2. 10 down to 1.\n3. Even numbers from 2 through 20.\n4. Indexes of a string `s`.\n\nAnswers:\n\n```java\nfor (int i = 0; i < 10; i++)\nfor (int i = 10; i >= 1; i--)\nfor (int i = 2; i <= 20; i += 2)\nfor (int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++)\n```"
