          "body": "### What You Are Learning\n\nYou are learning standard loop algorithms without arrays or ArrayLists.\n\n### Common Algorithm Roles\n\nCounter:\n\n```java\nint count = 0;\n```\n\nAccumulator:\n\n```java\nint sum = 0;\n```\n\nFlag:\n\n```java\nboolean found = false;\n```\n\nBest-so-far:\n\n```java\nint max = firstValue;\n```\n\n### Counting Example\n\n```java\nint count = 0;\nfor (int n = 1; n <= 100; n++)\n{\n    if (n % 7 == 0)\n    {\n        count++;\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Sum Example\n\n```java\nint sum = 0;\nfor (int n = 1; n <= 100; n++)\n{\n    sum += n;\n}\n```\n\n### Digit Processing Example\n\n```java\nint n = 5832;\nint count = 0;\nwhile (n > 0)\n{\n    int digit = n % 10;\n    if (digit % 2 == 0)\n    {\n        count++;\n    }\n    n /= 10;\n}\n```\n\n### Practice\n\nWrite code that counts how many integers from 1 through 500 are divisible by 3 but not by 5.\n\nCheckpoint condition:\n\n```java\nn % 3 == 0 && n % 5 != 0\n```"
