          "body": "### What You Are Learning\n\nYou are learning to traverse and analyze strings.\n\n### Character-by-Character Traversal\n\nUsing substring:\n\n```java\nfor (int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++)\n{\n    String ch = s.substring(i, i + 1);\n}\n```\n\nUsing `charAt` if available in context:\n\n```java\nfor (int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++)\n{\n    char ch = s.charAt(i);\n}\n```\n\nAP Quick Reference emphasizes `substring`, but code may show `charAt` in some practice materials.\n\n### Count a Character\n\n```java\nint count = 0;\nfor (int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++)\n{\n    if (s.substring(i, i + 1).equals(\"a\"))\n    {\n        count++;\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Count a Length-2 Pattern\n\n```java\nint count = 0;\nfor (int i = 0; i < s.length() - 1; i++)\n{\n    if (s.substring(i, i + 2).equals(\"an\"))\n    {\n        count++;\n    }\n}\n```\n\nStop at `s.length() - 1` because `i + 2` must not exceed `s.length()`.\n\n### Build a New String\n\n```java\nString result = \"\";\nfor (int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++)\n{\n    String ch = s.substring(i, i + 1);\n    if (!ch.equals(\" \"))\n    {\n        result += ch;\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Practice\n\nWrite code to:\n\n1. Count vowels.\n2. Count non-overlapping `\"aa\"` in a string.\n3. Build a string containing characters at even indexes."
