          "id": "4.11",
          "title": "2D Array Creation and Access",
          "unit": 4,
          "source": "Unit4_Detailed_Tutorials.md",
          "body": "### What You Are Learning\n\nYou are learning how to store data in rows and columns.\n\n### Mental Model\n\nA 2D array is an array of arrays.\n\nIt is often used like a table:\n\n```text\nrow 0:  3  5  7\nrow 1:  2  4  6\n```\n\n### Creating With Values\n\n```java\nint[][] grid = {\n    {3, 5, 7},\n    {2, 4, 6}\n};\n```\n\n### Accessing an Element\n\n```java\nSystem.out.println(grid[1][2]);\n```\n\nOutput:\n\n```text\n6\n```\n\nWhy?\n\n- `grid[1]` is row 1: `{2, 4, 6}`\n- `grid[1][2]` is column 2 in row 1: `6`\n\n### Row and Column Language\n\n```java\ngrid[row][col]\n```\n\nFirst index:\n\n```text\nrow\n```\n\nSecond index:\n\n```text\ncolumn\n```\n\n### Creating With Dimensions\n\n```java\nint[][] table = new int[3][4];\n```\n\nThis creates:\n\n```text\n3 rows\n4 columns per row\n12 total int values\n```\n\nDefault values are `0`.\n\n### Lengths\n\n```java\ntable.length\n```\n\nnumber of rows.\n\n```java\ntable[0].length\n```\n\nnumber of columns in row 0.\n\nFor rectangular 2D arrays, every row has the same length.\n\nAP CSA assumes rectangular 2D arrays. Nonrectangular 2D arrays are outside the exam scope.\n\n### Accessing One Row\n\nA single row of a 2D array is a 1D array.\n\n```java\nint[] rowOne = grid[1];\n```\n\nIf:\n\n```java\nint[][] grid = {{1, 2, 3}, {4, 5, 6}};\n```\n\nthen `grid[1]` is the array `{4, 5, 6}`.\n\n### Changing a Value\n\n```java\ngrid[0][1] = 99;\n```\n\nOriginal:\n\n```text\n3 5 7\n2 4 6\n```\n\nAfter:\n\n```text\n3 99 7\n2 4 6\n```\n\n### Practice\n\nGiven:\n\n```java\nint[][] nums = {{1, 2, 3}, {4, 5, 6}};\n```\n\nAnswer:\n\n1. What is `nums.length`?\n2. What is `nums[0].length`?\n3. What is `nums[1][0]`?\n\nAnswers:\n\n```text\n2\n3\n4\n```\n\n### AP-Style Checkpoint\n\nCreate a 2 by 3 `String` array named `seats`, then assign `\"Ada\"` to row 1, column 2.\n\nPossible answer:\n\n```java\nString[][] seats = new String[2][3];\nseats[1][2] = \"Ada\";\n```"
