          "id": "4.15",
          "title": "Sorting Algorithms",
          "unit": 4,
          "source": "Unit4_Detailed_Tutorials.md",
          "body": "### What You Are Learning\n\nYou are learning how to trace and understand selection sort and insertion sort.\n\nMerge sort is covered later in Topic 4.17 because it is recursive.\n\n### Why Sort?\n\nSorted data is easier to:\n\n- Search with binary search\n- Display in order\n- Find duplicates\n- Compare values\n\n### Selection Sort Mental Model\n\nSelection sort repeatedly selects the smallest remaining value and puts it in the next position.\n\n```text\nFind the smallest value from index 0 to end.\nSwap it into index 0.\nFind the smallest value from index 1 to end.\nSwap it into index 1.\nContinue.\n```\n\nSelection sort may also be written to select the largest remaining value and place it into its final position. The trace pattern is the same: find the next final value, then swap.\n\n### Selection Sort Code\n\n```java\npublic static void selectionSort(int[] arr)\n{\n    for (int i = 0; i < arr.length - 1; i++)\n    {\n        int minIndex = i;\n\n        for (int j = i + 1; j < arr.length; j++)\n        {\n            if (arr[j] < arr[minIndex])\n            {\n                minIndex = j;\n            }\n        }\n\n        int temp = arr[i];\n        arr[i] = arr[minIndex];\n        arr[minIndex] = temp;\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Selection Sort Trace\n\nArray:\n\n```text\n{5, 1, 4, 2}\n```\n\nPass 1:\n\n```text\nSmallest from index 0-3 is 1 at index 1.\nSwap index 0 and index 1.\n{1, 5, 4, 2}\n```\n\nPass 2:\n\n```text\nSmallest from index 1-3 is 2 at index 3.\nSwap index 1 and index 3.\n{1, 2, 4, 5}\n```\n\nPass 3:\n\n```text\nSmallest from index 2-3 is 4 at index 2.\nSwap index 2 with itself.\n{1, 2, 4, 5}\n```\n\n### Insertion Sort Mental Model\n\nInsertion sort builds a sorted left side.\n\n```text\nTake the next value.\nMove larger left-side values one position right.\nInsert the value where it belongs.\n```\n\n### Insertion Sort Code\n\n```java\npublic static void insertionSort(int[] arr)\n{\n    for (int i = 1; i < arr.length; i++)\n    {\n        int key = arr[i];\n        int j = i - 1;\n\n        while (j >= 0 && arr[j] > key)\n        {\n            arr[j + 1] = arr[j];\n            j--;\n        }\n\n        arr[j + 1] = key;\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Insertion Sort Trace\n\nArray:\n\n```text\n{5, 1, 4, 2}\n```\n\nPass with `i = 1`:\n\n```text\nkey = 1\n5 is greater than 1, shift 5 right.\nInsert 1 at index 0.\n{1, 5, 4, 2}\n```\n\nPass with `i = 2`:\n\n```text\nkey = 4\n5 is greater than 4, shift 5 right.\n1 is not greater than 4.\nInsert 4 at index 1.\n{1, 4, 5, 2}\n```\n\nPass with `i = 3`:\n\n```text\nkey = 2\n5 shifts right.\n4 shifts right.\n1 stays.\nInsert 2 at index 1.\n{1, 2, 4, 5}\n```\n\n### Selection vs Insertion\n\nSelection sort:\n\n```text\nFinds the next minimum.\nMakes one swap per outer pass.\n```\n\nInsertion sort:\n\n```text\nKeeps a sorted prefix.\nShifts values until the key fits.\n```\n\n### Sorting ArrayLists\n\nThe same selection-sort and insertion-sort ideas can be applied to an `ArrayList`.\n\nSelection sort with `ArrayList<Integer>`:\n\n```java\nfor (int i = 0; i < list.size() - 1; i++)\n{\n    int minIndex = i;\n\n    for (int j = i + 1; j < list.size(); j++)\n    {\n        if (list.get(j) < list.get(minIndex))\n        {\n            minIndex = j;\n        }\n    }\n\n    int temp = list.get(i);\n    list.set(i, list.get(minIndex));\n    list.set(minIndex, temp);\n}\n```\n\nThe algorithmic trace is the same as with arrays. Only the access syntax changes from `arr[i]` to `list.get(i)` and `list.set(i, value)`.\n\n### Practice\n\nTrace the first two passes of selection sort on:\n\n```text\n{3, 8, 2, 5}\n```\n\nAnswer:\n\n```text\nAfter pass 1: {2, 8, 3, 5}\nAfter pass 2: {2, 3, 8, 5}\n```\n\n### AP-Style Checkpoint\n\nDescribe the state of the left side of the array after each pass of insertion sort.\n\nStrong answer:\n\n```text\nAfter each pass, the elements from index 0 through the current index are sorted relative to each other.\n```"
